<font color="#FF0000">POST WAR TRAUMA</font><br>
<tt>Fri Dec 27 21:38:30 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I've been tying to put the war behind me since I returned home in July 1972. My first wife couldn't deal with my &quot;moods&quot; and left in 1976. It was smart of her to do so. Meditation has not worked for me nor did any form of medication (drugs and alcohol).<br><br>
The night mares are still as vivid as they were in 1971 and 1972. I try to live with them. The Vet Center here in KC,MO has been a big help for me to put the past in perspective.<br><br>
I don't try to bury the dreams any longer. I try to see them through. Is there a magic pill to end the dreams and pain? No! The answer Iv'e been told is to stop blaming myself for events that were beyond my control. I try, but with little success. I just try to live one day at a time.
